title: [CI] Add Travis CI conf for ROS Kinetic.
comments:
[{'user_id': 'dejanpan', 'created_at': '2017-11-22T20:58:05Z', 'comment_text': '@130s thanks for the PR. We in fact do not have an internal CI (other than 50+ developers building regularly on their work stations) and that is a major problem indeed which we are aware of.

However the problem is also not to setup a CI script (we could and are trying to do so on ROS buildfarm https://github.com/ros/rosdistro/pull/16449) but we need to make packages releasable as per autowarefoundation/autoware_ai#960 first.
So I would for now not accept this PR as I certainly do not need another CI server screaming at me for something I know very very well that we need to fix.

But I would happily accept help for making the Autoware packages releasable.

@130s since I already have you here - can you comment how `industrial_ci` is different from ROS buildfarm?'}, {'user_id': 'dejanpan', 'created_at': '2017-11-25T07:51:03Z', 'comment_text': '@130s I hope I didnt drive you away. Did you see my Q:
> can you comment how industrial_ci is different from ROS buildfarm?'}, {'user_id': '130s', 'created_at': '2017-11-29T14:07:47Z', 'comment_text': "@dejanpan That makes sense and like I mentioned I knew y'all have your priority.

> since I already have you here - can you comment how industrial_ci is different from ROS buildfarm?

That's on my todo stack and requires some more thoughts. I'll probably respond to that question by answering [this thread](https://answers.ros.org/question/273190/ci-recommendation/) or even more particularly, by editing [this wiki page](http://wiki.ros.org/CIs). In a nutshell the one provided by `ros.org` is the official so you're definitely encouraged to use that one. But I found that it doesn't cover everything, and requires rather a complicated setting. So usually I recommend using both ros.org and industrial_ci (which I normally do)."}]

a)

b) 
Use https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.1/module/FindXercesC.html to properly include headers and link https://github.com/CPFL/Autoware/blob/e79c5b03da7edbf933d1be1a949384d5bdb7b9db/ros/src/sensing/drivers/camera/packages/pointgrey/CMakeLists.txt#L44.

c) 
package.xml should build_depend and run_depend on:

- roscpp
-  std_msgs
-  message_generation
-  tf
- xerces (see: https://github.com/ros/rosdistro/blob/9ac4adcdb7205f1f6342fba3556e76eb588510e0/rosdep/base.yaml#L4549)
- cv_bridge

title: Feature/multiple crosswalk
comments:
[{'user_id': 'dejanpan', 'created_at': '2017-10-26T07:48:28Z', 'comment_text': '@yk-fujii how does this work? Does it check if any crosswalks intersect with the planned path?'}, {'user_id': 'yk-fujii', 'created_at': '2017-10-27T05:00:47Z', 'comment_text': 'It is applied by checking [Use Crosswalk Detection]and [Enable Multiple Crosswalk Detection] in the append window of velocity_set.

Conventionally, only [Use Crosswalk Detection] was existed.
[Use Crosswalk Detection] function control a velocity by detection pedestrians on the closest crosswalk with the planned path.

This feature add [Enable Multiple Crosswalk Detection] function.
[Enable Multiple Crosswalk Detection] function detect pedestrians on the multiple crosswalks with the planned path.
'}]

comments:

Add 2 lines below in the bottom of the CMakeLists.txt

And can you remove the unnecessary lines in the CMakeLists.txt?'}, {'user_id': 'dejanpan', 'created_at': '2017-08-25T06:02:34Z', 'comment_text': '@kitsukawa do you plan to merge this PR?

@ChenxiTU can you please describe how to run or test? 

Best would be if you reformat the description as this: https://github.com/CPFL/Autoware/blob/master/docs/pull-request-template.md'}, {'user_id': 'ChenxiTU', 'created_at': '2017-08-25T08:22:11Z', 'comment_text': "## Status
**PRODUCTION**

## Description
Real-time compressing/decompressing velodyne packet data. Date from HDL64E, HDL64ES2, HDL64ES3, HDL32E and VLP_16 are supported.  Compression ratio is around 1/3. Decompressed points may have a little bias which is less than 1cm.

## Related PRs
None.

## Todos
Sorry, I'm not sure about the meaning of Tests and Documentation. I do not cover the test data in the file.

## Steps to Test or Reproduce

Compression:
 Start compression node
`rosrun compression compress2png`
Then play your file which should have /velodyne_packets topic:
`rosbag play yourfile.bag`
Compression node will compress packet data into a new topic /velodyne_packets_compressed
You can use 
`rosbag record /velodyne_packets_compressed`
to get the compressed data.

Decompression:
Start decompression node
`rosrun compression recon2packet`
Then play the compressed data which should have /CompressedPacket topic:
`rosbag play compresseddata.bag`
Then a reconstructed  /velodyne_packets will be built 


"}]
